            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50773",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blanchon_vincent",
                        "name": "blanchon_vincent",
                        "displayName": "BLANCHON Vincent",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Can you add your routes, controller and Di configuration ?\r\n\r\nWith default route, ControllerLoader find a \"index\" controller, you must write Di alias or an \"index\" key in \"controller\" configuration. \r\n\r\nIf you just add \r\n{code}\r\n'My-App-Index' => 'MyApp\\Controller\\IndexController',\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nYour app can't work.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blanchon_vincent",
                        "name": "blanchon_vincent",
                        "displayName": "BLANCHON Vincent",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-26T16:06:45.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-26T16:06:45.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50775",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mech7",
                        "name": "mech7",
                        "displayName": "Chris de Kok",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually it does work with beta 4 with only this. But the documentation has a note:\r\nhttp:\/\/packages.zendframework.com\/docs\/latest\/manual\/en\/zend.mvc.quick-start.html\r\n\r\n\"Note\r\nZendSkeletonApplication ships with a \"default route\" that will likely get you to this action. That route basically expects \"\/{controller}\/{action}\", which allows you to specify this: \"\/zend-user-hello\/world\". We're going to create a route here mainly for illustration purposes, as creating explicit routes is a recommended practice. The application will look for a Zend\\Mvc\\Router\\RouteStack instance to setup routing. The default generated router is a Zend\\Mvc\\Router\\Http\\TreeRouteStack.\"\r\n\r\nWhich does not mention adding the controller to the configuration first before it can be found by the default route, which is confusing as ZF 1 will load controllers automatically not needing to add them to the config first.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mech7",
                        "name": "mech7",
                        "displayName": "Chris de Kok",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-26T19:01:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-26T19:01:52.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50776",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mech7",
                        "name": "mech7",
                        "displayName": "Chris de Kok",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Yes i understand this part is in the controller confguration but i think you are missing my point. My point is that the documentation is misleading as it explains that the default route will take me to this controller and action. Which it cannot untill i add it to the configuration.\r\nIt would be better to add this to the documentation so it is less confusing for end users.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mech7",
                        "name": "mech7",
                        "displayName": "Chris de Kok",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-26T19:22:00.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-26T19:22:00.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/50777",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blanchon_vincent",
                        "name": "blanchon_vincent",
                        "displayName": "BLANCHON Vincent",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Ok you use a configuration like :\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n'defaults' => array(\r\n      'controller' => 'My-App-Index',\r\n            'action'     => '???',\r\n),\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nSo if you defined \r\n{code}\r\n'My-App-Index' => 'MyApp\\Controller\\IndexController',\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nit's work ok. But without that, app cannot work, because ControllerLoader (based on ServiceManager) don't know what is the controller associated to 'My-App-Index' identifier.\r\n\r\nEvan Coury work on a feature based on the route \/module\/controller\/action and i think this feature will resolve this problem.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=blanchon_vincent",
                        "name": "blanchon_vincent",
                        "displayName": "BLANCHON Vincent",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2012-05-26T19:23:39.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2012-05-26T19:23:39.000+0000"
                },
